devdoc.author: ZenChain Team
devdoc.details: Stores encrypted mood/stress/sleep scores and tags on-chain

params.limit: Maximum number of entries to return

params.isPublic: Whether to participate in global stats

returns.entryId: The ID of the created entry

devdoc.title: ZenChainDiary - Encrypted Mental Health Diary

deleteEntry(uint256).notice: Soft delete an entry (marks as deleted, doesn't remove from chain)

entries(uint256).notice: Mapping from entry ID to entry

getEntry(uint256).notice: Get a diary entry (read-only, returns encrypted handles)

getEntryMoodScore(uint256).notice: Get encrypted mood score for an entry (workaround for Mock env struct field limitation)

getEntryMoodTags(uint256).notice: Get encrypted mood tags for an entry

getEntrySleepQuality(uint256).notice: Get encrypted sleep quality for an entry

getEntryStressScore(uint256).notice: Get encrypted stress score for an entry

getEntryTextHash(uint256).notice: Get encrypted diary text hash for an entry

getPublicEntryCount().notice: Get total number of public entries

getUserEntries(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Get user's entry IDs with pagination

getUserEntryCount(address).notice: Get total number of user entries

profiles(address).notice: Mapping from user address to profile

publicEntryIds(uint256).notice: Array of public entry IDs (for global stats)

updatePrivacySetting(bool).notice: Update privacy setting for participating in global stats

userdoc.notice: A privacy-preserving mental health diary using FHEVM
